cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the problem of generating accurate top-N recommendation lists for domains with graded relevance data. It also proposes a new metric, Graded Average Precision, for assessing the quality of ranked results list for graded relevance. 

It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a latent factor model, GAPfm, for optimizing Graded Average Precision. 

Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category as recommender systems are a common application of AI. 

Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) could also be a relevant sub-category as the paper proposes a fast learning algorithm that uses an adaptive item selection strategy to ensure scalability to large data sets. 

Finally, the paper could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as recommender systems are often used in social networks to suggest friends or content to users.
